title: Muppet Babies DVD QUALITY 107, 110 (Star Wars), 308 Muppets
description:
Muppet Babies DVD Quality
Episode 107: Eight Take-Away One Equals Panic 
Episode 110: Gonzo's Video Show
Episode 308: The Daily Muppet

As of this writing, the 1980s animated series Muppet Babies has never officially been released on DVD in the United States.

However, four episodes were released as giveaways with plush toys in 2003.

Here are three of them. These are Muppet Babies episodes in full DVD quality for you to enjoy.

The rare intros to the unsuccessful spinoff series Little Muppet Monsters - and the hourlong Muppets Babies and Monsters compilations - are also included, as restored from VHS. I've also included DVD trailers for The Dark Crystal, Labyrinth and Dog City.

(The fourth released episode, 202, Miss Piggy's Hyper Activity Book, is not included on this particular disc due to space considerations.)

-----

Muppet Babies
Episode 107: Eight Take-Away One Equals Panic
Air Date   October 27, 1984
Written by Jeffrey Scott

The Muppet Babies overhear Nanny talking to Mr. Jenkins on the phone, making cryptic references to "getting rid of one of them" in the nursery. They worry which of them will be thrown out. When Nanny seems to suggest that Fozzie is being taken away, they band together and declare that if he leaves, they will all leave. But they've misunderstood. Nanny reassures the babies that she will never stop caring for any one of them.

Song: "Table for One"

-----

Muppet Babies
Episode 110: Gonzo's Video Show
Air Date   November 17, 1984
Written by Jeffrey Scott

Gonzo borrows Nanny's camcorder and makes movies, including a Star Wars parody. Kermit says, "When we grow up, we might even have our own television show!" This episode was shown as a prime-time telvision special.

Song: "I Can't Help Being a Star"

-----

Muppet Babies
Episode 308: The Daily Muppet
Air Date	 November 1, 1986
Written by	Jeffrey Scott

After Nanny's newspaper gets too wet for her to read, the Babies decide to make their own newspaper for Nanny. Piggy writes a movie review, Fozzie does the comics, Rowlf writes a music review, Animal helps with the want ads, and Skeeter is in charge of sports. Meanwhile, Gonzo tries to get photos of aliens.

Song: "The Daily Muppet"

-----

Special Features:

Muppets, Babies and Monsters Opening Theme (restored from VHS)

Little Muppet Monsters Opening Theme (restored from VHS)

Trailers: The Dark Crystal, Labyrinth, Dog City
